md:
giải nghĩa từ "bt" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.
- bt (verb) : to beat, to strike, to hit
+ Meaning: Đánh, đập, tấn công
+ Example: He bt the ball with his racket.
+ Related words: hit, strike, beat, slap, punch

- bt (abbreviation) : better
+ Meaning: Tốt hơn
+ Example: This new phone is bt than the old one.
+ Related words: better, best, good, excellent

- bt (abbreviation) : between
+ Meaning: Giữa
+ Example: The meeting is bt 2pm and 3pm.
+ Related words: between, among, from, to

- bt (abbreviation) : but
+ Meaning: Nhưng
+ Example: I wanted to go, bt I was too tired.
+ Related words: but, however, although, though
